heat_3d_simple_imbal_nonres:

Compare pinning vs. work-stealing for balanced and imbalanced workloads
without resilience.

Command-line options:
  -ntiles <int>: Number of tiles in the domain (default 4)
  -tilesize <int>: Number of elements per tile in each dimension (default 8)
  -nsteps <int>: Number of time steps total (default 128)
  -[no]checksum: Whether or not to use checksums (default checksum)
  -inject <filename>: Failure list for failure injection (default disabled)
  -[no]imbalance: Whether or not to use imbalanced workload (default noimbalance)
  -[no]pin: Whether or not to pin tasks to workers (default nopin)

heat_3d_simple_nonres, heat_3d_simple_replay, heat_3d_simple_replic:

Analyze performance degradation introduced by chosen resilience mechanism.

Command-line options:
  -ntiles <int>: Number of tiles in the domain (default 4)
  -tilesize <int>: Number of elements per tile in each dimension (default 8)
  -nsteps <int>: Number of time steps total (default 128)
  -[no]checksum: Whether or not to use checksums (default checksum)
  -inject <filename>: Failure list for failure injection (default disabled)

heat_3d_simple_mix:

Mix replay and replication per the command-line configuration.

Command-line options:
  -ntiles <int>: Number of tiles in the domain (default 4)
  -tilesize <int>: Number of elements per tile in each dimension (default 8)
  -nsteps <int>: Number of time steps total (default 128)
  -replic <int>: Replicate last percentage of tasks (default 20)
  -[no]checksum: Whether or not to use checksums (default checksum)
  -inject <filename>: Failure list for failure injection (default disabled)

